            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Mercedes Benz International School is amongst the top international schools in the state of Maharashtra. It offers International Baccalaureate program for the students with world class education.This programmes are classifields in to three stages which are Primary Years Programme, Middle Years Programme and Diploma Years Programme.This school  enables students to excel in their careers.\nFaculty: The School have well qualified staff and faculty members with an aim to meet the academic and hostel needs of the students.\nAll admissions to MBIS are on first come first served basis. Generally, the admission procedure for the new school year is conducted during March/April. You are advised to contact the school admissions office as early as December and put in the application package for admission soon after. All the forms are filed in order of receipt and we are in a position to make new admission offers only if we have space in the class you are seeking admission too. This is normally confirmed by April/May. Payment of the Admission fee and Registration fee will confirm your admission to MBIS.Submission of form with supporting documents: School records for two years, copies of parent’s passport and any other information that you think is important for the school to have.\nAdmission form is reviewed, entrance test conducted wherever necessary. Seat to be reserved or confirmed on payment of fees. All admission to Mercedes-Benz International School are on first come first serve basis  and seat will be offered based on the availability in each class.\nAffiliated Board : International Baccalaureate program\nThe boarding facility is open to all students age 11 years and above\nFacilities which are offered by the school concludes of modern amenities like fully air-conditioned four-storey building with separate sections for boys and girls, Computers with Wi-Fi access and secure broadband internet connectivity,indoor games and gymnasium.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
